tmjos-defaults (1.3.0-3) noble; urgency=medium

  * Force X11 session via /etc/gdm3/custom.conf (WaylandEnable=false).
    Plank only supports X11; on Wayland it aborts at startup with
    "Only X11 environments are supported", leaving installed TMJOs
    systems with no dock. This is the root cause of the "wallpaper-only
    desktop" reported after v1.3.0-2 install.
  * Patch idempotent: re-running the postinst on already-patched
    systems is a no-op.
  * Note for v1.4+: replace Plank with a Wayland-native dock
    (gnome-shell-extension-dashtodock is the leading candidate).
    Plank is unmaintained since 2022 and Wayland is the future
    default in GNOME — X11 fallback is a v1.3.x bridge, not a
    long-term strategy.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Mon, 11 May 2026 11:55:00 -0300

tmjos-defaults (1.3.0-2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add 'tmjos-tweaks@tmjos.local' to org.gnome.shell enabled-extensions.
    This activates the TMJOs Tweaks extension shipped by
    tmjos-shell-tweaks 1.3.0-3 (hides Activities button via JS).

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Sun, 10 May 2026 21:35:00 -0300

tmjos-defaults (1.3.0-1) noble; urgency=low

  * Initial .deb release.
  * Replaces phase 6e of v1.2 customize.sh.
  * dconf override file installed to /etc/dconf/db/local.d/.
  * postinst runs dconf update so changes are picked up immediately.

